Carl I. DINGFELDER and Benjamin Balish, Copartners, Doing Business under the Firm Name of Dingfelder & Balish, Appellants, v. THE Steamship BRENTA II, Her Engines, etc., Navigazione Libera Triestina S. A., Appellee. Ramon J. BOERA and Alvaro Boera, Copart-ners, Doing Business under the Firm Name of Boera Brothers, Appellants, v. THE Steamship BRENTA II, Her Engines, etc., Navi-gazione Libera Triestina S. A., Appellee. Nos. 246, 247. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Feb. 5, 1934. Finkler & Finkler, of New York City (Frank I. Finkler, Jesse IT. Finlder, and Michael C. Bernstein, all of New York City, of counsel), for appellants. *1000Loomis & Euebush, of New York City (Homer L. Loomis, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decrees (-F. Supp.-) affirmed.
